President Uhuru Kenyatta today at state house Nairobi held talks with coast governors, Hassan, Joho, Amason Kingi and Salim Mvurya. Sources privy to the meeting told KTN news that the president read the riot act to the three governors from the coastal region against forming a regional party. Kilifi governor Amason Kingi had threatened to ditch ODM and unveil a coast region party next week Tuesday. however, Joho was opposed to the move saying the region&rsquo;s interests are well catered for in ODM. our senior political affairs reporter patrick amimo has the details.